   "source": [
    "# 📊 Lab 3A — Analyze a Query Log Dataset\n",
    "> **Block 3 | 20 Minutes | Data Source: OpenTelemetry Traces via Langfuse API**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## What This Lab Is About\n",
    "\n",
    "This version of Lab 3A replaces the static CSV file with **live OpenTelemetry trace data** pulled directly from the Langfuse observability platform running on HPE Private Cloud AI. Every RAG chain invocation you ran in Lab 2A generated a Langfuse trace. Those traces contain richer signal than a flat CSV — each record carries span-level latency, token counts, retrieval scores, model names, and user metadata.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the realistic production scenario: a platform engineer analysing RAG quality does not work from a pre-exported CSV — they query the observability platform directly and work with live trace data. The analysis pipeline (embed → cluster → UMAP → diagnose) is identical to the CSV version, but the data ingestion layer reflects real operational practice.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🔭 Why OpenTelemetry + Langfuse?\n",
    "\n",
    "| Signal | CSV Log | OTel / Langfuse Trace |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Query text | ✅ | ✅ |\n",
    "| Retrieval score | ✅ (top-1 only) | ✅ (full top-k score array) |\n",
    "| Latency | ❌ | ✅ (per span: retrieval, LLM, total) |\n",
    "| Token counts | ❌ | ✅ (input + output tokens) |\n",
    "| Model name | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
    "| Retrieved doc IDs | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
    "| User roles | ❌ | ✅ (from custom metadata) |\n",
    "| Session context | Partial | ✅ (full session trace tree) |\n",
    "| Real-time | ❌ | ✅ (live API) |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🎯 Learning Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "- Fetch RAG query traces from the Langfuse REST API\n",
    "- Parse nested OTel span data into a flat analysis dataframe\n",
    "- Embed query text into dense vectors using `sentence-transformers`\n",
    "- Apply K-means clustering to group semantically similar queries\n",
    "- Visualise clusters in 2D using UMAP dimensionality reduction\n",
    "- Identify content gap clusters by retrieval score analysis\n",
    "- Propose concrete pipeline improvements per gap cluster\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🗺️ Lab Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Cell | What You Are Building | Target Time |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Config | 1 | Langfuse credentials, parameters | 1 min |\n",
    "| Step 1 | 2–3 | Fetch traces from Langfuse API, flatten to dataframe | 3 min |\n",
    "| Step 2 | 4 | Embed 500 queries into 384d vectors | 3 min |\n",
    "| Step 3 | 5–6 | Elbow curve + K-means clustering | 3 min |\n",
    "| Step 4 | 7–8 | UMAP 2D visualisation (by cluster + by score) | 4 min |\n",
    "| Step 5 | 9 | Identify top 3 failure clusters | 3 min |\n",
    "| Step 6 | 10 | Write diagnosis and proposed fixes | 2 min |\n",
    "| Validate | 11 | Run full validation suite | 1 min |\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⚠️ Past 20 minutes and stuck? Open `03_solution.ipynb` — all cells are pre-run.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📡 Data Source: Langfuse Trace API\n",
    "\n",
    "Langfuse exposes a REST API at `/api/public/traces` that returns paginated trace records. Each trace corresponds to one RAG chain invocation and contains nested spans for retrieval, embedding, LLM inference, and output processing.\n",
    "\n",
    "The ingestion layer in this lab:\n",
    "1. Authenticates to Langfuse using Basic Auth (public key + secret key)\n",
    "2. Paginates through the traces endpoint to collect 500 records\n",
    "3. Extracts `input`, `output`, `scores`, and custom `metadata` from each trace\n",
    "4. Flattens the nested structure into a pandas dataframe with the same schema as the CSV version\n",
    "\n",
    "After Cell 3, the dataframe is **schema-identical** to the CSV version — all downstream cells (Steps 2–6) run unchanged."
   ]
  },
